      "role": "user",
      "content": "i was looking at some old photos today and i didnt even recognize the person looking back at me. not the face, but the look in their eyes. it's like that person actually died a long time ago and i'm just... walking around in their skin. just a shell of what i was supposed to be. it feels so heavy living like this.",
